<li id="cite_note-127"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-127">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFStevenson1882">Stevenson (1882)</a>; <a href="#CITEREFHale1834">Hale (1834</a>, pp.&#160;264–265); <a href="#CITEREFVan_Horn1881">Van Horn (1881)</a>; <a href="#CITEREFWhitmer1875">Whitmer (1875)</a> ("The plates were not before Joseph while he translated, but seem to have been removed by the custodian angel."). <a href="/wiki/Isaac_Hale" class="mw-redirect" title="Isaac Hale">Isaac Hale</a> said that while Joseph was translating, the plates were "hid in the woods" (<a href="#CITEREFHale1834">Hale 1834</a>, p.&#160;264). <a href="/wiki/Joseph_Smith_Sr." title="Joseph Smith Sr.">Joseph Smith Sr.</a> said they were "hid in the mountains" <a href="#CITEREFPalmer2002">Palmer (2002</a>, pp.&#160;2–5).</span>
