<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAnthon1834" class="citation cs2"><a href="/wiki/Charles_Anthon" title="Charles Anthon">Anthon, Charles</a> (February 17, 1834), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/stream/mormonismunvaile00howe#page/270/mode/2up">"Letter to Eber Dudley Howe"</a>, in <a href="/wiki/Eber_Dudley_Howe" class="mw-redirect" title="Eber Dudley Howe">Howe, Eber Dudley</a> (ed.), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/mormonismunvaile00howe"><i>Mormonism Unvailed: or, A Faithful Account of That Singular Imposition and Delusion, from Its Rise to the Present Time</i></a>, <a href="/wiki/Painesville,_Ohio" title="Painesville, Ohio">Painesville, Ohio</a>: Telegraph Press, pp.&#160;270–272</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Letter+to+Eber+Dudley+Howe&amp;rft.btitle=Mormonism+Unvailed%3A+or%2C+A+Faithful+Account+of+That+Singular+Imposition+and+Delusion%2C+from+Its+Rise+to+the+Present+Time&amp;rft.place=Painesville%2C+Ohio&amp;rft.pages=270-272&amp;rft.pub=Telegraph+Press&amp;rft.date=1834-02-17&amp;rft.aulast=Anthon&amp;rft.aufirst=Charles&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fstream%2Fmormonismunvaile00howe%23page%2F270%2Fmode%2F2up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGolden+plates" class="Z3988"></span>.</li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBennett1893" class="citation cs2"><a href="/wiki/James_Gordon_Bennett_Jr." title="James Gordon Bennett Jr.">Bennett, James Gordon Jr.</a> (June 25, 1893), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.sidneyrigdon.com/dbroadhu/NY/NYherld2.htm#062593">"Mormon Leaders at Their Mecca"</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/The_New_York_Herald" class="mw-redirect" title="The New York Herald">The New York Herald</a></i></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+New+York+Herald&amp;rft.atitle=Mormon+Leaders+at+Their+Mecca&amp;rft.date=1893-06-25&amp;rft.aulast=Bennett&amp;rft.aufirst=James+Gordon+Jr.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sidneyrigdon.com%2Fdbroadhu%2FNY%2FNYherld2.htm%23062593&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGolden+plates" class="Z3988"></span>.</li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBennett1831" class="citation cs2"><a href="/wiki/James_Gordon_Bennett_Sr." title="James Gordon Bennett Sr.">Bennett, James Gordon Sr.</a> (1831), <a href="/wiki/Leonard_J._Arrington" title="Leonard J. Arrington">Arrington, Leonard J.</a> (ed.), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://byustudies.byu.edu/content/james-gordon-bennetts-1831-report-mormonites">"James Gordon Bennett's 1831 Report on 'The Mormonites'<span class="cs1-kern-right"></span>"</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/BYU_Studies" title="BYU Studies">BYU Studies</a></i>, <b>10</b> (3): 353–364 (1–10 in reprint)</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=BYU+Studies&amp;rft.atitle=James+Gordon+Bennett%27s+1831+Report+on+%27The+Mormonites%27&amp;rft.volume=10&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.pages=353-364+%281-10+in+reprint%29&amp;rft.date=1831&amp;rft.aulast=Bennett&amp;rft.aufirst=James+Gordon+Sr.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbyustudies.byu.edu%2Fcontent%2Fjames-gordon-bennetts-1831-report-mormonites&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGolden+plates" class="Z3988"></span>.</li>
